// ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
//  Global Blur Quality (applies to every background blur)
//  Docs: https://github.com/niri-wm/niri/wiki/Configuration:-Miscellaneous#blur
//  Noctalia: https://docs.noctalia.dev/v5/compositor-settings/niri/
// ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
//
//  Tuning recipe (wiki): raise `offset` first (free) until artifacts,
//  then raise `passes` by one to smooth them. Repeat.
//
//  On NVIDIA RTX 5050, xray blur is cheap: niri blurs the wallpaper
//  once and reuses it. Non-xray (realistic) blur costs more but is
//  handled well by this GPU. We use non-xray for Noctalia surfaces
//  (configured in layer-rules.kdl) for the most realistic look.
blur {
    passes 4
    offset 5.0
    noise 0.02
    saturation 1.6
}
